    { question: "What is Google Business Profile (formerly GMB)?", answer: "Google Business Profile is the free listing that appears when someone searches for your business or your trade on Google and Google Maps. It was previously called Google My Business (GMB), and many tradesmen still use that name. It shows your business name, star rating, review count, phone number, website, opening hours, photos, and service area. For local tradesmen, it\'s the most important piece of online real estate you have — it appears above all website results in local searches, meaning it\'s often the first and only thing a customer sees about your business before deciding whether to call." },
